                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/8680: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-06T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 6—1:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>213. Mission of Far Eastern Republic presents strong protest against recent
                    Japanese <hi rend="italic">coup</hi> in Vladivostok, states it considers all
                    nations participating in Allied intervention in Siberia are equally responsible
                    for grave consequences of that intervention and hopes that the United States
                    will consider it its duty to do everything in its power to effect early
                    withdrawal of Japanese troops from Russian territory. Mission states similar
                    protest being lodged with the British Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
